Description: A shallow pottery dish or cover, made of coarse red-brown siltware with a surface red slip. The slip has been polished by pebble-burnishing, and on the exterior this has been executed in concentric stripes. Much of the slip has been lost through flaking of the surface.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), Findspot 32, under the floor of chamber 19 A
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 32 has been scratched into the base.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.91, fig.4, p.109, p.197, pl.39)
